         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne: May 29th 1889. ¶ My Dear Baron, ¶  ¶ I have been here with an invalid wife, and I am very sorry to be obliged to leave without seeing you, who have done so much for botany, scientific and p...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.05.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From A. M. Ferguson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M: 'Answ 31/5/89'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found in a copy of A.M. &amp; J. Ferguson (1887) <seg style="font-style: italic; ">India rubber and gutta percha …</seg>, London.</p>
               </note>Melbourne: May 29th 1889.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My Dear Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have been here with an invalid wife, and I am very sorry to be obliged to leave without seeing you, who have done so much for botany, scientific and popular. We go on board the Oceana at Williamstown to morrow evening and sail for Ceylon at 1 o'clock on Friday.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I send for your acceptance a couple of books published at my Office — that of the Ceylon Observer.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With all good wishes,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours Sincerely,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A M Ferguson.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
